  "prompt": "Can you be allergic to meat and fish?",
  "response": "Yes, meat and fish allergies do exist:\n\n1. Meat Allergies:\n- Red meat allergy (alpha-gal syndrome) can be caused by tick bites\n- Some people develop allergies to specific types of meat like beef, pork, or lamb\n- Symptoms can include hives, swelling, and anaphylaxis\n\n2. Fish Allergies:\n- One of the most common food allergies\n- Can involve specific types of fish or multiple varieties\n- Often a lifelong allergy\n- Can cause severe reactions like anaphylaxis\n\n3. Similar Allergies:\n- Shellfish allergy is also common\n- Some people are allergic to specific proteins in meat or fish\n\n4. Symptoms:\n- Skin rashes\n- Swelling\n- Difficulty breathing\n- Digestive issues\n- Potentially life-threatening reactions\n\n5. Diagnosis:\n- Skin prick tests\n- Blood tests\n- Supervised food challenges\n\nAnyone suspecting a meat or fish allergy should consult an allergist for proper diagnosis and management.",
